rComments: I took introduction course to Women and Gender studies with Professor Lord. She is a nice prof, however gives many readings. If you attend lectures and do all the readings, and if you are interested in topic, this course will be easy for you. Also, she doesn't give any surprises on tests and exam, she is really fair and you know what to expect.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'So many papers', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: The textbook was really interesting, but her lectures were so boring.

rComments: She couldn't articulate what she was saying most of the time. Seemed unprepared for the lectures and left everyone extremely confused by the end of it. Good intentions and passionate about what she was talkingg about but bad execution.
She is knowledgable about the course material well, but can be very disorganized.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Although she seems like an approachable person and will help you if asked, her lectures were horrible. She treats her lecture as if it is a high school class, and I left the lectures more confused then when I walked in. Her stuttering and disorganization suggests little preparation and leads you to question why you even show up to class.
Although Prof. Lord is very passionate about what she teaches, her teaching style can be a bit confusing and all over the place. Despite this, she seems like a friendly and approachable person.
